cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with visual question answering (VQA), which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new task of VQA-E, which involves generating explanations for answers, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. The paper uses a multi-task learning architecture and conducts a user study, indicating the use of machine learning (ML) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely sub-categories.
